    Text

Listen & Repeat: DECIDE

Download

You’ll hear each sentence once, then the word as it sounds in the full sentence three times.  Then you’ll hear fragments:  the word linking into the word before, and the word linking into the word before and after.  You’ll hear the word and fragment three times, repeat each time.  Focus on how the word sounds in the context of the whole sentence and how it links into the words around it.  Finally, you’ll hear the sentence three times.  Repeat each time.  

WHAT TO FOCUS ON:  Focus on how the word sounds in sentences: stressed with the up and down inflection of the voice (the shape of stress). Feel how it smoothly links into the words around it.

Sentences:

  1. We can’t decide what show to watch.
  2. Don’t let me decide for you.
  3. Who decides what should be in the curriculum?
  4. I hope he decides to come with us.
  5. She decided to bring her sister.
  6. Have they decided who they are going to hire?
  7. We’re having trouble deciding.
  8. We’ve decided to stay another night.
  9. I’ve decided against it.
  10. They haven’t decided yet.
  11. I’ve decided to study law.
  12. We’re deciding where we want to eat.
  13. I think you should decide.
  14. They decided on a red car.
  15. I’ve decided to quit smoking.

Click the DOWNLOAD ICON above to save a copy to your device.
